# Source of truth

Full map: [`docs/source-of-truth-map.md`](../../docs/source-of-truth-map.md)

## Task readiness

Use `toTaskReadinessInput()` + `deriveTaskState()` from `@/lib/task-readiness`.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — parallel blocking logic
if (task.status === "TODO" && openIssues.length) { ... }

// ✅ GOOD
const state = deriveTaskState(toTaskReadinessInput(task, stageContext), liveSignals, {
  recoveryFlowIssueId: task.recoveryFlow?.jobIssueId,
});
```

Server completion must go through `completeJobTaskAction`, not ad-hoc status updates to DONE.

## Payments

Use `@/lib/job-payment-readiness` for operational due-ness and holds.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — raw status for gating
if (req.status === "DUE") { blockWork(); }

// ✅ GOOD
if (isPaymentEffectivelyDue(req, ctx)) { ... }
```

Display labels may use `job-payment-display.ts`. Do not add stored payment blocker flags on tasks.

## Workstation attention

Extend `queryWorkstationWorkItems()` and `rank()` — do not create a second queue builder.

## Quote / lead progress

- Quotes: `getQuoteReadiness()`, `evaluateQuoteJobActivationReadiness()`
- Leads: `getLeadCommercialProgress()` — progress is derived, not stored on Lead

## Issues / recovery

All resolve paths through `resolveJobIssueWithRecoveryHandling()` with explicit mode (`standard` | `resume` | `force`).

## Activity

Significant mutations call `recordJobActivity()`.

## Theme

Use semantic tokens (`text-foreground-muted`, `bg-surface`, `border-border`). No raw `zinc-*` / `gray-*` / `slate-*` classes.
